Project2

Class Priority

  • java.lang.Object
    • Project2.Priority

  • public class Priority
extends java.lang.Object

    3.Create a class named Priority that implements a priority queue of state objects using an array, based on population, highest population is the highest priority. Support the following methods:

    [Priority(int)]a. Constructor that creates the stack array based on a size provided.

    [insert(State)]b. An insert method to insert a state into the queue.

    [remove()]c. A remove method to remove a state from the front of the queue and return it.

    [printQueue()]d. A print Queue method to print the queue in priority order, see the example.

    [isEmpty()]e. An isEmpty method that returns true if the queue is empty, false otherwise

    [isFull()]f. An isFull method that returns true if the queue is full, false otherwise

    Version:
    10/13/17
    Author:
    Ryan Geddings N01067534
